cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.collection

Class DynamicCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.collection.Collectible
      • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.collection.Collection
        • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.collection.DynamicCollection

  • public class DynamicCollection
extends Collection
    DynamicCollections contain a ContentSearch object which is executed upon defining the ContentSearch. DynamicCollections may initially be created as empty "shell" objects that have not yet defined the searchCriteria property for. Once the searchCriteria is declared (either by calling setSearchCriteria(cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.ContentSearch) or by passing it to the class constructor) however, the actual search is immediately executed by calling the IProductAPI.searchContent(cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.ContentSearch) method and passing the search criteria object. Returned matching Content items are wrapped as ContentProxy objects because they inherit from Collectible. By executing the search criteria as soon as it is defined the DynamicCollection will have children objects available immediately after defining the search criteria, which aids in iteration (see also CollectionIterator).
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    David Killeffer <rayden7@gmail.com>
